ÎÎµÏ. Î¹Î³Î. â CHAP. XIII.

Prophets and teachers are here spoken of as resident
ministers, entitled to maintenance. They were to have
the first-fruits of everything. Î£Î¹ÏÎ¯Î±, in Classic Greek,
is the plural of ÏÎ¹ÏÎ¯Î¿Î½, meaning âfoodâ in general.
Here, as in the Byzantine Greek, it is a singular noun,
and means âbatch,â or âbaking of bread.â

